The station was opened in August 1908 by a German consortium, Anatolia-Baghdad Corporation.
Germany, a delay in imperial play, wanted to realize its ambitions to dominate the Middle East through this railway that ran to Damascus, Baghdad and beyond what Saudi Arabia is today.
